Oyo State Police Command has paraded some suspected kidnappers for allegedly killing a minor in Saki town. The development was conveyed through a press statement issued by the state Police Public Relations Officer, SP Adewale Osifeso. Copy of the statement made available to Journalists stated that “It is an established fact that Oyo State Police Command maintains a Zero tolerance Policy towards crime and all sorts of criminality. Wike Killing Genuine Businesses In Rivers -Dakuku Peterside Police To Probe Killing Of Tenant In Ekiti The Dragnet of the Oyo State Police Command on Monday 07/03/2022 caught up with the Duo of Abdulrazak Waliu ‘m’ age 23yrs and Abdulrazak Illias ‘m’ age 18yrs who allegedly abducted and murdered an eight-year-old minor. On 5th March, 2022 at about 0800hrs one Bamimore Abdulafeez ‘m’ reported that on 04/03/2022 at about 1200hrs when his twin children one Bamimore Abdulraheem ‘m’ and Bamimore Abdullahi ‘m’ returned from school. One of them named Bamimore Abdulraheem went out of the house after being lured by the duo of Abdulrazak Waliu and Abdulrazak Illias to an undisclosed location, and all effort made to see the victim proved abortive. On 07/03/2022 a search party was organised and in the process, the lifeless body of the victim named Bamimore Abdulraheem ‘m’ aged 8yrs was found inside an uncompleted building at Alubarika area Saki. Upon interrogation, Abdulrasak Ilias ‘m’ and Abulrasak Hammid ‘m’ all confessed to having conspired to kidnap the victim for ransom but eventually killed him because he recognised and could identify them. Further updates on the incident would be provided in due course as the investigation continues.